researchers at the university of washington studied the telerobot raven ii . they found that robots designed for surgery could be ` easily ' hacked in . this is because they are operated over public networks which allowed the researchers to access them and stop them working . this enabled them to change the speed of the arms of the robot and change their orientation , making it impossible for the machines to carry out a procedure as directed .
