palaeontologists in china say the impeccably preserved fossil belongs to a small dinosaur thought to have lived 160 million years ago . the strange-looking creature had small stiff feathers on its body and long finger-like bones extending from each wrist that were covered in a membrane like a bat 's wing . the discovery has provided new insight into how vertebrates first began to take to the air .
