toyal lotus technology stops yoghurt from sticking to lids of pots . the ` spooner ' who scrapes the remaining yoghur back into the pot , and the ` waster ' who throws it away . this is inspired by the water-repellent nature of a lotus leaf . these bumps increase the contact angle at which droplets touch the surface , which in turn force the droplets to form into spheres .
